---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="PCT Protocols Guide">
  <main class="container mx-auto px-4 py-8 max-w-4xl">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Post Cycle Therapy (PCT) Protocols</h1>

    <div class="prose max-w-none">
      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-500 p-4 mb-8">
        <p class="text-blue-700">
          Post Cycle Therapy (PCT) is crucial for maintaining gains and restoring natural hormone production after an anabolic steroid cycle. This guide provides comprehensive protocols for effective recovery.
        </p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">Understanding PCT</h2>
      <p class="mb-6">
        PCT is designed to help your body restore its natural testosterone production after a cycle of anabolic steroids. Without proper PCT, you risk losing gains and experiencing prolonged hormonal imbalance.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">When is PCT Needed?</h2>
      <div class="bg-gray-100 p-6 rounded-lg mb-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">PCT is required after:</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
          <li>Any cycle containing testosterone</li>
          <li>Most injectable anabolic steroids</li>
          <li>Oral steroid cycles</li>
        </ul>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-4 mb-3">PCT may not be needed for:</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
          <li>TRT (Testosterone Replacement Therapy) if continuing</li>
          <li>Some specific compounds (consult healthcare provider)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">Standard PCT Protocols</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-white shadow-md rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Basic Protocol (8 weeks)</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
            <li>Weeks 1-2: Nolvadex 40mg daily</li>
            <li>Weeks 3-4: Nolvadex 30mg daily</li>
            <li>Weeks 5-6: Nolvadex 20mg daily</li>
            <li>Weeks 7-8: Nolvadex 10mg daily</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white shadow-md rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Advanced Protocol (with Clomid)</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
            <li>Weeks 1-2: Nolvadex 40mg + Clomid 50mg daily</li>
            <li>Weeks 3-4: Nolvadex 30mg + Clomid 25mg daily</li>
            <li>Weeks 5-6: Nolvadex 20mg daily</li>
            <li>Weeks 7-8: Nolvadex 10mg daily</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">Timing Your PCT</h2>
      <div class="bg-yellow-50 border-l-4 border-yellow-500 p-4 mb-8">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">When to Start PCT</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
          <li>Short-ester testosterone: 3 days after last injection</li>
          <li>Long-ester testosterone: 2 weeks after last injection</li>
          <li>Nandrolone or Trenbolone: 2-3 weeks after last injection</li>
          <li>Oral steroids: 24 hours after last dose</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">PCT Medications</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Primary Medications</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
            <li>Nolvadex (Tamoxifen)</li>
            <li>Clomid (Clomiphene)</li>
            <li>HCG (pre-PCT)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Supporting Supplements</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
            <li>Vitamin D3</li>
            <li>Zinc</li>
            <li>Magnesium</li>
            <li>Fish Oil</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">Recovery Optimization</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">During PCT:</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
          <li>Maintain caloric intake at maintenance or slight surplus</li>
          <li>Continue regular training with moderate intensity</li>
          <li>Ensure adequate sleep (8+ hours)</li>
          <li>Manage stress levels</li>
          <li>Monitor for signs of low testosterone</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">Monitoring Recovery</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <p>Get bloodwork to check:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
          <li>Testosterone levels (Total and Free)</li>
          <li>Estradiol</li>
          <li>LH and FSH</li>
          <li>Complete metabolic panel</li>
          <li>Lipid profile</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4">Recommended testing schedule:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
          <li>Pre-cycle baseline</li>
          <li>Mid-cycle (if running longer cycles)</li>
          <li>6-8 weeks after PCT completion</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-500 p-4 mt-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Important Warnings</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
          <li>Never start a cycle without having PCT medications on hand</li>
          <li>Avoid alcohol during PCT</li>
          <li>Watch for signs of depression or mood changes</li>
          <li>Seek medical attention if experiencing severe side effects</li>
          <li>Consider time between cycles (Time on + PCT = Time off)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
